[h1]The Math Object[/h1]

The Math object allows you to perform mathematical tasks, and includes several properties. [img id="2767" width="100%"]
[b]For example:[/b][code format="js" codeId="701"]document.write([b]Math.PI[/b]);
//Outputs 3.141592653589793[/code]
[note]Math has no constructor. There's no need to create a Math object first.[/note]

[h1]Math Object Methods[/h1]

The Math object contains a number of methods that are used for calculations: [img id="2769" width="100%"]
For example, the following will calculate the [b]square root[/b] of a number.[code format="js" codeId="702"]var number = Math.[b]sqrt[/b](4); 
document.write(number);
//Outputs 2[/code]

[h1]The Math Object[/h1]

Let's create a program that will ask the user to input a number and alert its square root.[code format="js" codeId="703"]var n = prompt("Enter a number", "");
var answer = Math.sqrt(n);
alert("The square root of " + n + " is " + answer);[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2770" width="100%"]
Enter a number, such as 64. [img id="2771" width="100%"]
